- quay.io/condaforge/linux-anvil-x86_64:alma9

  r-base:

about.summary: Feature Ordering by Conditional Independence (FOCI) is a variable selection algorithm based on the measure of conditional dependence. For more information, see the paper: Azadkia and Chatterjee (2019),"A simple measure of conditional dependence" <arXiv:1910.12327>.

Feature Ordering by Conditional Independence (FOCI) is a variable selection algorithm based on the measure of conditional dependence. For more information, see the paper: Azadkia and Chatterjee (2019),"A simple measure of conditional dependence" <arXiv:1910.12327>.

name: r-foci
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.1.3' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-foci
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/FOCI_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/FOCI/FOCI_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 1c0472a93f4e26b59e3cb8c8be307621f41abd11bc8a4285446103954c295d45

build:
  number: 4
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}    # [build_platform != target_platform]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-rann
    - r-data.table
    - r-gmp
    - r-proxy
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-rann
    - r-data.table
    - r-gmp
    - r-proxy

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('FOCI')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('FOCI')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=FOCI
  license: GPL-3.0-only
  summary: 'Feature Ordering by Conditional Independence (FOCI) is a variable selection algorithm
    based on the measure of conditional dependence. For more information, see the paper:
    Azadkia and Chatterjee (2019),"A simple measure of conditional dependence" <arXiv:1910.12327>.'
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
